the singing cosmonaut sees something in the window&nbsp;
moving outside of the ship and toward the hatch.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:39.840 --> 00:00:45.360
Later, a parachute is seen in the sky over Soviet&nbsp;
Kazakhstan. A man on a horse approaches the fallen&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:50.000
spaceship. He lights a flashlight and finds one&nbsp;
of the cosmonauts dead on the side of the ship.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:53.680
The other one is crawling out of the&nbsp;
ship, barely finding his footing,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:53.680 --> 00:00:57.200
as the man approaches him. When&nbsp;
the cosmonaut raises his head,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:57.200 --> 00:01:00.080
blood is coming out of his mouth&nbsp;
and his eyes are completely black.&nbsp;

00:01:00.640 --> 00:01:05.920
A woman is seen entering a conference room in&nbsp;
the Research Institute for Brain AMS in Moscow.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:05.920 --> 00:01:10.880
The room is being prepared for a hearing. The&nbsp;
board members come in and the hearing begins.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:10.880 --> 00:01:15.600
Tatyana is being investigated about an&nbsp;
injury she possibly inflicted on a patient.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:19.600
Her colleagues from the board don't doubt her&nbsp;
methods, but still think that a certain level of&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:19.600 --> 00:01:24.400
negligence should be considered. She disagrees,&nbsp;
saying that the she did what needed to be done&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:30.320
on a misdiagnosed patient. A man is observing the&nbsp;
hearing and later approaches Tatyana in the lobby.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:34.880
He introduces himself as Colonel Semiradov&nbsp;
and asks for her consulting help on a patient,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:34.880 --> 00:01:39.360
saying that he also runs a form of research&nbsp;
institute. She is a little apprehensive,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:39.360 --> 00:01:43.760
but becomes interested as he tells her&nbsp;
that he's also involved in neuropsychiatry.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:43.760 --> 00:01:47.600
Semiradov tells her that he will take her to see&nbsp;
the patient, but if she doesn't want to work the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:47.600 --> 00:01:53.280
case, he'll bring her back. On the way there in a&nbsp;
helicopter, they talk about the patient. She asks&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:58.400
for his medical files, but instead he gives her an&nbsp;
oral report. He tells her that the patient is one&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:58.400 --> 00:02:03.440
of the cosmonauts from Orbita-4 and explains that&nbsp;
certain things were left out of the media. Kostya&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:03.440 --> 00:02:08.400
appears to be suffering from episodic amnesia, not&nbsp;
remembering the incident that happened in space,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:08.400 --> 00:02:13.520
before the ship landed. She asks if she should&nbsp;
sign a non-disclosure agreement, considering that&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:19.360
the cosmonaut, a Soviet national hero, might have&nbsp;
lost his mind. They arrive in Kazakhstan and take&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:24.720
a car to the a Scientific Research institute. Once&nbsp;
there, Semiradov informs her that she can move&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:24.720 --> 00:02:29.440
freely in 90% of the institute and after she gets&nbsp;
her clearance she could get into the restricted&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:35.520
area as well. They enter an elevator which takes&nbsp;
them to an observational room. Meanwhile, Kostya&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:35.520 --> 00:02:40.400
is being hypnotized by a psychiatrist. Tatyana&nbsp;
observes the session from the other side of the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:40.400 --> 00:02:45.520
glass. The psychiatrist wants to get information&nbsp;
out of the cosmonaut, but he just kids with him.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:49.520
The doctor gets angry, saying he can't&nbsp;
help him if he doesn't let him help.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:49.520 --> 00:02:54.400
The man coughs and the doctor gets unnerved.&nbsp;
Kostya tells him that he can't be hypnotized,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:59.600
since only the most mentally strong can be sent to&nbsp;
space. Doctor Rigel walks into the other side of&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:05.120
the room, greeted by Semiradov who tells Tatyana&nbsp;
that he's the research director of the institute.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:05.120 --> 00:03:09.520
The cosmonaut bangs on the window and asks&nbsp;
what has happened to his colleague. Tatyana&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:09.520 --> 00:03:13.840
asks what Colonel Semiradov needs and he tells&nbsp;
her that he needs her opinion on his condition.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:18.880
She walks on the other side of the window&nbsp;
and introduces herself. Kostya is happy for&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:18.880 --> 00:03:24.720
the change from Rigel. She offers him some tea,&nbsp;
which he takes and drinks. Tatyana observes all&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:29.280
of his movements and tells him why she's there,&nbsp;
then asks him about the toy in the corner. He&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:34.080
replies that it's his, something having to do&nbsp;
with cosmonaut traditions. She asks him what&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:34.080 --> 00:03:38.960
happened during the mission, but he's weary of&nbsp;
doing it again. Since she hasn't read the files,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:38.960 --> 00:03:42.720
he still tells her that the mission went&nbsp;
without a glitch until the landing procedure,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:42.720 --> 00:03:47.520
after which he can't remember anything, part&nbsp;
from waking up in the Institute. He realizes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:47.520 --> 00:03:52.080
that she can't help him get out of there, so when&nbsp;
she says that she can at least help him, Kostya&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:52.080 --> 00:03:56.400
gives her the name and number of his mother asking&nbsp;
Tatyana to inform her that he's alive and well.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:57.040 --> 00:04:01.280
She takes the tea and before she leaves, says&nbsp;
that it was a pleasure to meet him. When she&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:01.280 --> 00:04:06.560
hands the teacup to Rigel it burns his hands and&nbsp;
she explains to the Colonel that Kostya has PTSD&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:11.280
and that his sensory receptors or peripheral&nbsp;
nervous system might be damaged. After giving&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:11.280 --> 00:04:16.000
her evaluation, she asks to leave. Semiradov&nbsp;
tells her that she can leave in the morning.&nbsp;

00:04:16.720 --> 00:04:20.480
The soldier taking her to her room tells her&nbsp;
that the Colonel would need to authorize her&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:20.480 --> 00:04:26.160
departure tomorrow. As they walk, they see a few&nbsp;
people working under supervision. To her question&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:26.160 --> 00:04:31.280
about them, the soldier replies that they are&nbsp;
prisoners, brought in to do hard labor. He takes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:31.280 --> 00:04:36.640
her to her room and says she's the only one in the&nbsp;
building. Tatyana gets into her room and unpacks,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:36.640 --> 00:04:41.040
then wants to make an outside call, only to be&nbsp;
told that no one can make those from the base,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:41.040 --> 00:04:47.040
except Semiradov. That night, she's taking a bath&nbsp;
and a giant scar is seen on her back. She takes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:47.040 --> 00:04:52.720
some pills for the pain and goes to bed, but since&nbsp;
she can't sleep she goes out for a run. Suddenly,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:57.840
she runs into one of the prisoners. Once back&nbsp;
in her room, there's a knock on the door. It's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:04:57.840 --> 00:05:03.520
Semiradov. He takes her back to the observation&nbsp;
room and asks her when was the last time she ate.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:08.560
When she replies, he checks his watch and gives&nbsp;
the order to start. A glass window comes down in&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:08.560 --> 00:05:13.680
the cosmonauts chambers and more soldiers come in,&nbsp;
securing the door. Tatyana and the others watch&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:19.120
the security cameras as something starts happening&nbsp;
to Kostya's body. Suddenly, he falls from the bed&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:19.120 --> 00:05:24.640
and something is coming out of his mouth. The&nbsp;
blob transforms into an alien creature. Tatyana&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:29.760
is shocked. Semiradov asks her if she wants&nbsp;
to take a closer look. She goes to the glass&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:29.760 --> 00:05:35.360
window and waits for a sight of the creature.&nbsp;
It appears. She observes it and it observes her.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:40.400
Tatyana reaches her hand out to it, but it jumps&nbsp;
at the window. She goes out of the room shocked&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:46.160
and terrified. Semiradov runs to her and tells her&nbsp;
the creature is non-terrestrial. Tatyana wants to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:46.160 --> 00:05:50.640
know if Kostya is aware that it lives inside&nbsp;
of him, but that doesn't seem to be the case.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:50.640 --> 00:05:54.560
The Colonel wants her to find a way to separate&nbsp;
the host from the parasite or she could leave and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:54.560 --> 00:05:59.440
sign the non-disclosure agreement. She asks why&nbsp;
he chose her for the task and he answers that it&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:05:59.440 --> 00:06:05.040
is because she is willing to take risks. In his&nbsp;
mind that would save their national hero. Tatyana&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:05.040 --> 00:06:10.080
asks for the videotapes of the creature, Kostya's&nbsp;
testimony and all the notes they have. She will&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:06:10.080 --> 00:06:15.040
need to have two sessions a day with him, one hour&nbsp;
each. The Colonel is content to have her stay.&nbsp;

